# Backend conventions

## Structure
- HTTP routes live under **`app/api/v1/`** (one module per domain). Register them only in **`app/api/v1/router.py`** — `main.py` includes a single `api_router` with prefix `/api/v1`.
- **`GET /api/v1/meta`** — public **JSON** bootstrap only: `environment` (**`APP_ENV`**), **`features.intelligence`** (**`FEATURE_INTELLIGENCE`**, legacy **`FEATURE_AI_INTELLIGENCE`** accepted). **Not** a webhook endpoint — no POST ingest (e.g. Meta/social). Frontend caches this; do not duplicate toggles only in UI.
- Shared FastAPI deps (e.g. DB session, **`require_auth_user`** / **`AuthUser`** for cookie JWT): **`app/api/deps.py`**. Settings: **`app/core/config.py`**. Engine/session factory: **`app/db/session.py`** — do not open ad-hoc engines in route files.
- Legacy monolith pipeline (status FSM, team dropdown rules, ₹196 gate helpers, IST): **`app/core/pipeline_rules.py`**, **`app/core/pipeline_legacy.py`**, **`app/core/legacy_status_bridge.py`**, **`app/core/time_ist.py`**, **`app/core/row_utils.py`**; combined re-exports **`app/core/legacy_helpers.py`**. Current API **`Lead.status`** remains the small set in **`app/core/lead_status.py`** — use the bridge when importing old status strings.
- **Execution enforcement** (funnel, follow-up pressure, at-risk, leak map): **`app/services/execution_enforcement.py`**; routes **`app/api/v1/execution.py`** — `GET /execution/personal-funnel` (team), `GET /execution/follow-up-attack`, `GET /execution/downline-stats` (leader), `GET /execution/at-risk-leads`, `GET /execution/weak-members`, `GET /execution/leak-map`, `POST /execution/stale-redistribute` (admin; redistribute stub until `stale_worker` columns exist), `GET /execution/lead-ledger` (stub).
- **Reliability** (incident codes, structured ops logs): **`app/core/reliability.py`**. Unhandled 500 responses include optional **`error.incident_id`** alongside **`request_id`** (`app/core/errors.py`).
- **Monolith `services/`:** Verbatim under **`backend/legacy/myle_dashboard_main3/services/`** (`rule_engine`, `wallet_ledger`, `scoring_service`, `hierarchy_lead_sync`, `day2_certificate_pdf`). Ports under **`app/services/`** — `rule_engine` re-exports **`pipeline_rules`**; others match legacy behavior where SQLite/legacy schema applies; **`reportlab`** required for Day 2 PDF.

## Errors & tracing
- Failed responses use **`{"error": {"code", "message", "request_id"}}`** (see `app/core/errors.py`). `X-Request-ID` is set on every response (`app/middleware/request_id.py`); CORS exposes that header.
- Prefer **`HTTPException`** with a short **`detail`** string; handlers map status → **`code`** (e.g. 401 → `unauthorized`).

## API surface
- **No duplicate routes** for the same method + path (check existing routers before adding).
- Prefer **one** health-style surface: `/health` and `/health/db` as already defined — don’t add parallel “ping” endpoints without a reason.
- New domain = **new router module** (e.g. `app/api/v1/leads.py`) + `include_router` — avoid a second “god” `main.py` with dozens of `@app.get`.

## DB / migrations
- Schema changes = **SQLAlchemy model** + **Alembic revision** — keep model and migration in sync; don’t hand-edit prod DB without a migration story.
- **Legacy SQLite (old Flask `leads.db`) → Postgres:** offline CLI **`scripts/import_legacy_sqlite.py`** (run from **`backend/`**, same **`DATABASE_URL`** as API); mapping **`legacy/LEGACY_TO_VL2_MAPPING.md`**; ops notes **`backend/README.md`**. Not an HTTP route.

## Secrets & config
- No secrets in code — use **env** (`Settings` / `DATABASE_URL`, etc.). `.env` stays gitignored; document keys in **`.env.example`** only.
- **Auth cookies:** `myle_access` (short-lived JWT) + `myle_refresh` (rotation via `POST /api/v1/auth/refresh`). Tune **`JWT_ACCESS_MINUTES`**, **`JWT_REFRESH_DAYS`**. **`POST /api/v1/auth/login`** (bcrypt + `hashed_password`) and dev-login both set both cookies; **`POST /api/v1/auth/logout`** clears them. **`AUTH_LOGIN_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE`** limits POSTs to login/dev-login/refresh (0 disables).
- **`POST /api/v1/auth/dev-login`** is **off** unless `AUTH_DEV_LOGIN_ENABLED=true`. Production must leave it **false** and use real auth instead. When enabled, it loads the **`users`** row for `dev-{role}@myle.local` (seeded by Alembic) and issues JWTs with **`sub` = user id** and optional **`email`** claim on the access token.
- **Identity refresh (legacy `refresh_session_user`):** **`POST /api/v1/auth/sync-identity`** — requires access cookie; reloads **`users`** row and re-issues access + refresh JWTs. Helpers: **`app/core/auth_context.py`**, **`app/core/auth_cookies.py`**.
- Domain progress is tracked in **`docs/MYLE_VL2_CHECKLIST.md`** — add a checklist line when opening a new surface, then implement the router + schema (no orphan routes).
- **Leads:** **`app/api/v1/leads.py`** — `GET` (scoped + `limit`/`offset` + optional **`q`**, **`status`**, **`archived_only`**, **`deleted_only`** — recycle bin, **admin only**; mutually exclusive with **`archived_only`**; default list **active, non-pool, non-deleted**), `POST`, `PATCH`/`DELETE` by id (owner or **admin**). **`DELETE`** = soft delete (**`deleted_at`**, clears **`in_pool`**). **`PATCH`**: **`archived`**, **`in_pool`** (admin only; archive clears pool), **`restored: true`** (admin, clears **`deleted_at`**). **`POST /leads/{id}/claim`** — take a **pooled** lead. **`LeadPublic`**: **`archived_at`**, **`deleted_at`**, **`in_pool`**. **`app/api/v1/lead_pool.py`** — **`GET /lead-pool`** (pooled, non-archived, non-deleted). Status values: **`app/core/lead_status.py`**. Model **`app/models/lead.py`**, schemas **`app/schemas/leads.py`**.
- **Retarget:** **`app/api/v1/retarget.py`** — `GET` paginated list of non-archived leads with `status` in **lost** / **contacted**, same scope as leads.
- **Follow-ups:** **`app/api/v1/follow_ups.py`** — `GET` (join lead name; `open_only`); `POST` (`lead_id` must be visible); `PATCH` / `DELETE` by id. Model **`app/models/follow_up.py`**, visibility via **`app/services/lead_access.py`**.
- **Workboard:** **`app/api/v1/workboard.py`** — `GET` (same visibility as leads; **active** leads only — **`archived_at`**, **`deleted_at`**, **`in_pool`** filtered out; `columns[]` with `total` + `items` per status; query **`limit_per_column`**, **`max_rows`**). Shared scope helper **`app/services/lead_scope.py`**.
- **Team:** **`app/api/v1/team.py`** — **`GET /team/members`** (admin); **`GET /team/my-team`** (leader); **`GET /team/enrollment-requests`** (admin + leader); **`GET /team/reports`**, **`GET /team/approvals`** (admin stubs, **`SystemStubResponse`**). Schemas **`app/schemas/team.py`**.
- **System:** **`app/api/v1/system.py`** — **`GET /system/training`**, **`GET /system/decision-engine`** (admin); **`GET /system/coaching`** (admin + leader). **`SystemStubResponse`**: **`items`**, **`total`**, optional **`note`** (V1 empty lists). Schema **`app/schemas/system_surface.py`**.
- **Analytics:** **`app/api/v1/analytics.py`** — **`GET /analytics/activity-log`**, **`GET /analytics/day-2-report`** (admin). Response shape **`SystemStubResponse`** (shared stub schema).
- **Wallet:** **`app/api/v1/wallet.py`** — **`GET /wallet/me`** (balance + recent lines); **`GET /wallet/ledger`** (paginated; admin optional **`user_id`**); **`POST /wallet/adjustments`** (admin, signed **`amount_cents`**, **`idempotency_key`** unique, **`IntegrityError`** replay-safe). Model **`app/models/wallet_ledger.py`**, schemas **`app/schemas/wallet.py`**, migration **`20250410_0010_wallet_ledger.py`**.
- **Execution / Finance stubs / Other / Settings:** **`execution.py`**, **`finance_surfaces.py`**, **`other_pages.py`**, **`settings_pages.py`** — admin- or role-gated **`GET`**s returning **`SystemStubResponse`** for remaining nav parity (not product logic v1).
